Type_of_Forest_at_Site: Mostly evergreen trees (for example, pine or live oak)
Location_Relative_to_Slope: At the bottom of the slope or in a valley between slopes

Site_Comments: The site is divided from south to north by the silver lake ditch such that west of the ditch there is a semi-arid foothills ecosystem that gets only natural precipitation.  East of the ditch are clumps of siberian elms, populars, and plums and apple trees, which were part of an orchard 50-80 years ago and our 2 story house dating from the 1920s.  The area is only watered by irrigation from the ditch during the summer and only when it becomes so dry that the mixture of native and non-native grasses may die.
